Rating: 4
This orange lattice crust is my go-to recipe for all fruit pies - peach, apple and berry. It's great for a novice baker. It was my first homemade crust ever, and I return to it when I need to make sure my crust will be perfect.

Rating: 4
I made straight apple pie, without the dried fruit. The slight citrus flavor the orange juice added to a normally bland crust was great. It was served it at a Thanksgiving gathering, and everyone loved it.

