Very much enjoyed the pie as a 'change' from the same 'ol same 'ol. Cardomon adds a lovely flavour but the dried fruit seemed almost non-existant. In the future I will use sugar instead of honey and perhaps use an old fashion recipe for crust.

Rating: 4
Ok, I made this again--four times. It's wonderful! The crust is perfect everytime, and the fruit ads a nice zing when you bite into a piece. I still don't like the honey though, I use sugar to taste. The best apple pie ever!

Rating: 4
A great pie. The fresh orange juice added a unique flavor to the crust. Chilling the pie dough in the freezer for about 15 to 20 minutes is all it takes. Also, I eliminated all the fruit except the apples and the pie was still delicious. Adding a small amount of brandy or apple brandy adds to the flavor.

Rating: 3
This is a great pie. It's time consuming but worth the work.